<item>
            <title>[LU-200] clients in large directories loop forever when sending readpage request</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-200</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The reason for this problem is the ldlm hash handling is done with Lustre 2.X is incompatible with Lustre 1.8.X clients &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre 1.8.5.55 clients on cray and non cray hardware. Lustre 2.X on servers from April 5 checkout. One MDS and four OSS, each OSS has 7 OSTs. CentOS5.5 environment. This bug only occurs between 1.8 &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; 2.X</environment>
        <key id="10565">LU-200</key>
            <summary>clients in large directories loop forever when sending readpage request</summary>
